- **CLI Commands**: Use `mvn clean install` to build your project.
- **Latest Versions**: Ensure you are using the latest stable version of Spring Cloud Stream, e.g., `3.2.0.RELEASE`.
- **Key Config Options**:
  - Define an error handler in your configuration file (e.g., `application.yml`):
    ```yaml
    spring:
      cloud:
        stream:
          bindings:
            input:
              destination: myInputTopic
              group: myGroup
              consumer:
                errorHandler: myErrorHandler
    ```
  - Implement the error handler class:
    ```java
    @Component
    public class MyErrorHandler implements ErrorHandler {
        @Override
        public void handleError(Message<?> message, Throwable throwable) {
            // Custom error handling logic here
        }
    }
    ```
  - Use `@StreamListener` to handle messages and include error handling:
    ```java
    @Service
    public class MyService {

        @StreamListener(Sink.INPUT)
        public void handleMessage(String message) throws Exception {
            if (message.contains("error")) {
                throw new RuntimeException("Simulated error");
            }
            // Process the message
        }

        @StreamListener(Sink.ERROR)
        public void handleError(Message<?> errorMessage) {
            // Handle errors here
        }
    }
    ```
